OL,5, Government borrowing hit its highest   
OL,6, November level on record last month,   
OL,7, driven by the cost of supporting       
OL,8, households with the rising cost of     
OL,9, living and energy bills.               
OL,11,FBorrowing, the difference between      
OL,12,Fspending and tax income, reached #22bn,
OL,13,Fa rise of #13.9bn on November 2021.    
OL,15,FInterest on government debt also surged
OL,16,Fby 50.1% to #7.3bn.                    
OL,18,FThe Office for National Statistics     
OL,19,F(ONS) said inflation was the main      
OL,20,Ffactor behind the rise in borrowing.   
